HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 226
By Littleton
A RESOLUTION to honor Linda P. Hayes, former mayor of White
Bluff.
WHEREAS, it is our privilege to honor those devoted public servants who made great
strides in improving the lives of the citizens they so ably served; and
WHEREAS, one such individual is Linda P. Hayes, who held the post of mayor of White
Bluff for seventeen years until taking her retirement in 2024; and
WHEREAS, born and raised in the White Bluff community, Mrs. Hayes attended
Nashville State Technical Institute, now Nashville State Community College, and Austin Peay
State University; and
WHEREAS, Mayor Linda Hayes brought tremendous growth and progress to White
Bluff, helping establish the Jennie Woodworth Library and serving as a driving force behind the
new White Bluff Town Hall, the Fire Hall and 24-Hour Ambulance Station, and the Bibb-White
Bluff Civic Center; and
WHEREAS, Mrs. Hayes's long list of contributions includes serving as a member of the
White Bluff Planning Commission and the White Bluff Town Council, which she served from
1999 to 2007; she was also a member of the Tennessee Municipal Bond Fund Board, the Joint
Economic and Community Development Board of Dickson County, and the Economic and
Community Development Board of White Bluff; and
WHEREAS, Linda Hayes devoted her time and resources to the Dickson County Three
Star Committee, the Governor's Local Government Planning Advisory Committee, the Jennie
Woodworth Library Committee, the White Bluff Land Use and Transportation Committee, and
the White Bluff Strategic Growth Committee; and
