WHEREAS, a highly regarded leader throughout the State, Linda Hayes was a
Tennessee House of Representatives candidate for District 78 in 2012, and from 1999 to 2007,
she served the White Bluff community as vice mayor; and
WHEREAS, in addition to her experience in municipal administration, Linda Hayes
managed both commercial and residential growth and development in the White Bluff proper
township from 2007 to 2024; and
WHEREAS, duly honored for her commercial impact, Mrs. Hayes was named the
Dickson County Business Woman of the Year in 2009; and
WHEREAS, her professional accomplishments aside, Mrs. Hayes is most grateful for the
love and support she shares with her husband, Kenneth, and her children, Tracy, Jennifer, and
Ken; and
WHEREAS, it is most fitting that we recognize this esteemed public servant for her many
indelible contributions to the community she so selflessly served; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor former mayor Linda P. Hayes for more than two decades of
service to the good people of White Bluff, extending our best wishes for continued success in
her future endeavors.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
